caption: Good and affordable Indian food very close to campus. I had so many meals there when I was in school. I would recommend it in a heart beat.

We ordered saag paneer and veg biryani. The vegetable was fine but the biryani was SO SOUR, we had to throw it all away. When we informed them, he feigned ignorance saying "don't know why... We can't do anything about it. We don't do replacement or anything like that" Anybody with basic understanding of cooking knows that sour means OLD - I doubt that someone who is in this business for so long doesn't know "why"! AVOID! There are better Indian restaurants in Chicago with better food and better customer service.

I ordered through an app in an effort to actually to try to give patronage to the restaurants, and as someone of Indian descent, this was one of the most unappealing and cringeworthy experiences. I ordered the most simple dish of all, chicken biryani. It was basically just rice with very dry chicken breast and evidently what passes for sautéed onion. A good biryani doesn't even take much effort and I am saddened to think what the other menu items are if this basic dish cannot be mastered in any form. I will never order from here again.
my mom works here and shes a very hard worker very kind and pacinet with her orders and the food here us great!

We’ve been picking up dinners here since they opened a few years ago. Consistent. I can’t give better praise to a restaurant- so consistent, tasty and smart portions. And chicken 65?! Sold. Always worth the special treat!
Consistently good. Always on fire.

I feel curry on fire has become better overtime. The biryani is flavourful and my favourite. I have tried a couple of other options like chole, dal makhni, a variety of breads and have never been disappointed.
you will not be disappointed in the menu and service. the staff was sociable and attentive. this place has a good design. they have so many great reviews for a reason.
Makes me feel like I in Nashville again.
Next time I'll be back with my coworkers. Prices are fair I would say. If it was closer to my home I would be here often.
(Translated by Google) Tasty is delicious, but it is really Indian.  (Original) 好吃是好吃的，但是确实很印度。
I think I might become a regular.

I am picky about Indian dishes and am a harsh critic. This restaurant amazes me every time I taste a new dish. They seem to know the inherent nature of spices and combinations that enhance or tease the taste bud experience. Enjoy the ambiance as it is simple yet conveying the subtle nature of being in the company of Indians who don't care who is around when discussing movies or cricket.  I recently ordered a take out and was surprised at the change in taste and completeness of the dishes. Mirchi bajji picture on the menu shows traditional pepper/chilli with batter but what was served was pieces of pepper battered and fried with no resemblance to a mirchi bajji. Chicken 65 retained its taste. Chicken curry tasted funny. I ordered 2 butter naans and was not included in the take out. When i called, they were insisting the naan was in the bag. I lost my temper because the tone sounded that i was lying. When i can afford a tip for a take out, why would i lie about missing items that cost only $4. The owner needs to pay attention to quality and service they provide.
Consistently excellent Indian cuisine!  Dishes are spiced to perfection!  Curry on fire is highly recommended!
This place is so delicious! Love getting take out. Always dependable and so good!
Worst chana masala ever.

The space is cozy clean and staff friendly, however the food is fair but the quantity was soooo skimpy, i purchased large eggplant and received 2 cherry sized eggplant in nothing but bland gravy. I visited the restaurant prior and this time I WILL NOT EVER RETURN, spent 45.00$ and super unhappy.

Although I am not sure if it was the restaurant fault or grubhub, I would like to share my frustration. My husband and I never ever order online food, as we are always up to cook it ourselves, we are trying to help restaurants in this dark time.  So on Friday afternoon, when the restaurant indicated it was open and accepting orders, we placed one. It first said that the delivery would happen within 1 hour. Then shortly after we got another text saying 1:30 hour. Then after 2 hours we started calling the restaurant but no one ever answered.  Then we spent 30 more minutes with grubhub trying to get our money back.  I mean, whom’s fault it that? We were trying to help.

Charming setting, food is good. Manchurian Cauliflower is clear standout. Also the Pav Bhaji and Malai Kofta. Their Kashmiri Naan is amazing. Coronation Chicken, Daal Gosht. When they say it's spicy, believe them :). Poori was a little over-fried. Keema Samosa meat is a little dry.

The service was good. I personally did not like the food. It wasn’t bad Indian food. It was just bad food in general. I got the keema somosas, lamb biryani, and rose lassi. The somosas were dry and the meat in the biryani was chewy and the rice was plain. The ritta for the biryani was an extra $4, and it was essentially watered down yogurt, no cumbers, carrots, or flavor.

The serving size for the entree is quite small for the price, can do better with that. Overall taste is average. The staff is nice and friendly.

The waiters  cooperated in a graceful style, the meals were yummy and my friends were very  delighted. We shall absolutely come back again for more events. thanks very much.

I ordered food from Uber Eats to my hotel, and there were no utensils. The food was lukewarm. The naan bread was supposed to have raisins, but I didn’t taste them. It was bland. We visited yesterday. The restaurant was quite busy since it was Sat. But oh my, food and service are great. The server is absolutely AMAZING! It was our first time there, and we had millions of questions. But she patiently, smilingly answered them all. She also apologized in advance that the kitchen may take longer than normal to prepare the main dishes. So we asked for an appetizer, and the cauliflower dish she suggested was delishhhh. BEST DECISION ever. I also love how she tried to adjust the spice level of the curries for us. Our curry sauce was awesome, but the meat was quite dry. I will surely come back, because of the service and the cauliflower one. Highly recommended for first time tryer!

Nice Indian place right near the UIC in downtown Chicago. The place is really small, so it looks crowded even if there are 2 ot 3 people.
